						<div class="postbody">$10 ram sticks in a cart would be far more expensive then $0.50 chips with a $75 payment for the programmer. Plus, there's no reason for more RAM in carts, 32K WRAM is more then enough with SXROM, even if you can exhaust the 8K WRAM in most other RAM games. If you need more, you should consider moving to another more advanced system or making more optimized use of the RAM. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

